   {
      "body" : ">  (i.e. only re-download the blocks that have been pruned).\r\n\r\nIt would be useful to be able to re-download other ranges, especially when importing older wallets that need partial rescanning, but realize that the pruned part is always going to be a negligible part of the chain. E.g. the last 550Mb of >80GB. So it's not that big of a win when the goal is to switch back to full chain hosting.",
