   {
      "body" : "For reference, is there a way to calculate the least amount of disk space necessary such that a pruned node set to 550 will never run out of space? For example, I've been experimenting syncing to a 2.49 GB RAM disk to avoid the heavy disk I/O on a laptop, and when spot checking it, the free space may have gotten below 500MB once or twice, but that's only what I've happened to have seen.  I've got enough RAM to expand the RAM disk a bit more, but I have no idea what would be sufficient.",
      "created_at" : "2017-03-15T11:38:21Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/7097#issuecomment-286716835",
      "id" : 286716835,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/7097",
      "updated_at" : "2017-03-15T11:38:21Z",
      "url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/comments/286716835",
      "user" : {
         "avatar_url" : "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/8298277?v=3",
         "events_url" : "https://api.github.com/users/mmortal03/events{/privacy}",
         "followers_url" : "https://api.github.com/users/mmortal03/followers",
