      }
   },
   {
      "body" : "@mmortal03 The [bitcoin data](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/files.md) directory consists, globally, of:\r\n- Configuration files: trivial\r\n- Logging files: bounded at 10MB if the node is regularly restarted, otherwise it may grow larger, though with default debug settings this is only very slowly.\r\n- UTXO database=chainstate: large ~3GB at the moment\r\n- Block index: small, ~64MB at the moment\r\n- Block storage and undo files: huge ~110GB at the moment\r\n- Temporary state storage (banlist, mempool, etc): a few MB, max size of mempool can be configured\r\n\r\nAll of these except for the UTXO database, block index and block files are bounded. When pruning is enabled that also guarantees that \"block storage and undo files\" won't exceed the set threshold. What is left is:\r\n- The block index is small, a few bytes per block, so pretty much irrelevant in this equation.\r\n- The UTXO database is forever-growing and has to be completely stored at all times. This is the potentially problematic one here, which is why UTXO database growth and UTXO spam is considered such a serious issue.",
      "created_at" : "2017-03-15T11:49:56Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/7097#issuecomment-286719272",
      "id" : 286719272,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/7097",
      "updated_at" : "2017-03-15T11:49:56Z",
      "url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/comments/286719272",
      "user" : {
