   {
      "body" : "If your goal is to avoid disk i/o during syncing a better choice than a RAM disk is to pump up `-dbcache` to a big number, say, 8000. The full amount of memory that you have available. This makes sure the entire initial sync will happen in the cache and will only sync to disk afterwards.",
