   {
      "body" : "> One thing that comes to mind is that I closed and re-opened Core a few times along the way, so, might it be that once you close Core and open it back up, you've lost the benefit of whatever was in the dbcache during those previous sessions for good?\r\n\r\nPart of it - it indeed won't pre-populate the cache at startup, so only entries that are updated will go back to the cache.",
